get_photos

public JSONObject get_photos(java.lang.String feature,
                             java.lang.String[] only,
                             java.lang.String[] exclude,
                             java.lang.String sort,
                             java.lang.String sort_direction,
                             int page,
                             int rpp,
                             int image_size,
                             boolean include_store,
                             boolean include_states,
                             boolean tags)
500px GET_photos. Returns a listing of twenty (up to one hundred) photos for a specified photo stream.

Parameters:
(required) - feature photo stream to be retrieved. Default fresh_today. One of the constant in Class 'Features'.
only - String array of names of the category to return photos from. Must be one of the constant in Category.
exclude - String name of the category to exclude photos by. Must be one of the constant in Category.
sort - Sort photos in the specified order. Must be one of the constant in Sort.
sort_direction - Control the order of the sorting. You can provide a sort_direction without providing a sort, in which case the default sort for the requested feature will be adjusted. Must be one of the constant in SortDirection.
page - Return a specific page in the photo stream. Page numbering is 1-based.
rpp - The number of results to return. Can not be over 100, default 20.
image_size - The photo size to be returned. It has to be an integer: 1 to 4.
include_store - True to returns market information about the photo.
include_states - True to returns state of the photo for the currently logged in user and authenticated request.
tags - True to returns an array of tags for the photo.
Returns:
JSON response. See 500px API for details.

Parameters:
(required) - feature photo stream to be retrieved. Default fresh_today. One of the constant in Class 'Features'.
only - String array of names of the category to return photos from. Must be one of the constant in Category.
exclude - String name of the category to exclude photos by. Must be one of the constant in Category.
sort - Sort photos in the specified order. Must be one of the constant in Sort.
sort_direction - Control the order of the sorting. You can provide a sort_direction without providing a sort, in which case the default sort for the requested feature will be adjusted. Must be one of the constant in SortDirection.
page - Return a specific page in the photo stream. Page numbering is 1-based.
rpp - The number of results to return. Can not be over 100, default 20.
image_size - The photo size to be returned. It has to be an integer: 1 to 4.
include_store - True to returns market information about the photo.
include_states - True to returns state of the photo for the currently logged in user and authenticated request.
tags - True to returns an array of tags for the photo.
Returns:

get_photo_id

public JSONObject get_photo_id(java.lang.String id,
                               int image_size,
                               boolean comments,
                               int comment_page,
                               boolean tags)
500px GET_photos_id. Returns detailed information of a single photo in full photo format. Will return additional fields if photoInterface is constructed with valid access token.

Parameters:
id - id of data of photo to return.
image_size - Should be 1 to 4 while 1 being smallest.
comment - set to true to include comments of the photo in response. Comments are returned in order of creation, 20 entries per page.
comment_page - return the specified page from the comments listing. Page numbers are 1-based.
tags - returns an array of tags for the photo.
items - additional parameter for GET_photos_id request. Follow 500px github for more details.
Returns:
JSON response. See 500px API for details.

get_photos_search

public JSONObject get_photos_search(java.lang.String term,
                                    java.lang.String tags,
                                    Location geo,
                                    java.lang.String[] only,
                                    int page,
                                    int rpp,
                                    boolean showTags,
                                    int image_size,
                                    java.lang.String sort)
500px GET_photos_search. returns a listing of twenty (up to one hundred) photos from search results for a specified tag, keyword, or location.

Parameters:
term - a keyword to search for.
tags - a complete tag string to search for.
geo - a geo-location point of the format latitude,longitude,radius. Acceptable units are km or mi. (Example format 23.00,123.00,20km)
only - an array of String constant defined in category to return photos from. Note: Case sensitive.
page - return a specific page. Page numbering is 1-based.
rpp - the number of results to return. Can not be over 100, default 20.
showTags - returns an array of tags for each photo.
image_size - the photo size to be returned. It has to be an integer: 1 (smallest) to 4 (largest).
sort - one of the sort order constant defined in sort.
Returns:
JSON response. See 500px API for details.

post_photos_upload

public JSONObject post_photos_upload(Uri imagePath,
                                     java.lang.String name,
                                     java.lang.String description,
                                     int category,
                                     boolean privacy,
                                     java.lang.String shutter_speed,
                                     java.lang.String focal_length,
                                     java.lang.String aperture,
                                     int iso,
                                     java.lang.String camera,
                                     java.lang.String lens,
                                     java.lang.String latitude,
                                     java.lang.String longitude)
500px POST_photos_upload. Upload a photo to 500px. This feature is currently in beta by 500px and is subject to change. If your photo contains EXIF and IPTC tags, you can skip technical parameters.

Parameters:
imagePath - (required) - Photo filename in JPG/JPEG in Uri format.
name - Title of the photo.
description - Description for the photo.
category - A numerical ID for the Category of the photo as defined in Category.
privacy - Whether to hide the photo from the user profile on the website. Otherwise, the photo is only available for use in Collections/Portfolio.
shutter_speed - Shutter speed in seconds, represented by string containing a rational expression if the value is 1sec.
focal_length - Focal length in millimetres, a string representing an integer value.
aperture - Aperture value in integer format. There is no need to add f/ as prefix.
iso - ISO value.
camera - Make and model of the camera. Note: Please make sure it contains sensible information (eg., does not contain camera's make or model twice)
lens - Lens used to make this photo.
latitude - Latitude, in xxxx.xxxx format.
longitude - Longitude, in xxx.xxxx format
Returns:
JSON response. See 500px API for details.

Remark: Requires OAuth authentication.
